<p>Everest Base Camp trek, is one of the best treks in the world that centres on the world&#8217;s highest peak Mt. Everest (29,029 ft/ 8,848.68m). This trek (5,364m /17,598ft) will provide you with a natural thrill as it takes you through breathtaking high-altitude landscapes, Buddhist monasteries, traditional Sherpa culture, high-altitude animals, and snow-capped mountains, lakes. EBC is located at the height of(5,364m /17,598ft).</p>



<h2>&nbsp;</h2>



<h2 class="has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color"><span style="color: #6ec1e4;"><b>Highlights of Everest Base Camp Trek</b></span></h2>



<ul><li>Stay at the Base camp of Mount Everest at a height of (5,364m /17,598ft) with majestic mountain surrounding you.</li><li>Worldâ€™s highest airport at a height of 3,780m / 12.402ft).</li><li>Explore the interesting culture of Local Sherpa people staying in there.</li><li>Witness the sun setting&nbsp; over&nbsp; Everest from Kalapatthar&nbsp;which is&nbsp; also known as Eevrest viewpoint at a height of(5,555m).</li><li>Ancient Monastery at Tengboche (3,867m / 12,687ft).</li><li>Witness the beauty of Khu,mbu Glacier and Khumbu Icefalls.</li><li>Explore Sagarmatha national park with its wild range of flora and fauna.</li><li>View of other peaks like Mt. Lhotse(8,516m), Cho Oyu (8,201m) and Mt. Makalu (8,463m).</li></ul>



